  "body": "*Title*: *x-forwarded-client-cert doesn't forward SAN DNS names, only one URIName record is forwarded*\r\n\r\n*Description*:\r\nA certificate can support multiple DNS names through SAN but XFCC header is only forwarding URI name type and ignoring all DNS name types.\r\n\r\nExample SAN from certificate\r\nX509v3 Subject Alternative Name:\r\nURI:https://example.com, DNS:example.com, DNS:www.example.com\r\n\r\n[optional *Relevant Links*:]\r\nCode link: https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/568d90b787539e627e58b17f9643c27171b485a8/source/common/ssl/ssl_socket.cc#L266\r\n\r\nI am not 100% sure whether it's intended functionality or bug but as per [RFC 2818](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2818#section-3.1), SAN DNS names are useful in TLS verification. \r\n",
